types.name: BorshFeeRateLimiter
docs: we denote reference_amount = x0, cliff_fee_numerator = c, fee_increment = i
if input_amount <= x0, then fee = input_amount * c
if input_amount > x0, then input_amount = x0 + (a * x0 + b)
then fee = x0 * (c + c*a + i*a*(a+1)/2) + b * (c + i * (a+1))
if a = max_index + d, input_amount = x0 + max_index * x0 + (d * x0 + b)
then fee = x0 * (c + c*max_index + i*max_index*(max_index+1)/2) + (d * x0 + b) * MAX_FEE

fields.name: pool_creator_authority
docs: Only pool_creator_authority can use the current config to initialize new pool. When it's Pubkey::default, it's a public config.

fields.name: config_type
docs: Config type mode, 0 for static, 1 for dynamic

fields.name: sqrt_price
docs: The init price of the pool as a sqrt(token_b/token_a) Q64.64 value. Market cap fee scheduler minimum price will be derived from this value

fields.name: sqrt_price
docs: The init price of the pool as a sqrt(token_b/token_a) Q64.64 value

fields.name: whitelisted_vault
docs: Whitelisted vault to be able to buy pool before activation_point

fields.name: _padding
docs: padding, previous reserve amount, be careful to use that field

fields.name: activation_point
docs: Activation point, can be slot or timestamp

fields.name: activation_type
docs: Activation type, 0 means by slot, 1 means by timestamp

fields.name: collect_fee_mode
docs: 0 is collect fee in both token, 1 only collect fee only in token b

fields.name: version
docs: pool version, 0: max_fee is still capped at 50%, 1: max_fee is capped at 99%

fields.name: base_fee
docs: Trade fees are extra token amounts that are held inside the token
accounts during a trade, making the value of liquidity tokens rise.

fields.name: protocol_fee_percent
docs: Protocol trading fees are extra token amounts that are held inside the token
accounts during a trade, with the equivalent in pool tokens minted to

docs: Stores the state relevant for tracking liquidity mining rewards

fields.name: initialized
docs: Indicates if the reward has been initialized

fields.name: _padding_1
docs: Padding to ensure `reward_rate: u128` is 16-byte aligned

fields.name: funder
docs: Authority account that allows to fund rewards

fields.name: last_update_time
docs: The last time reward states were updated.

fields.name: cumulative_seconds_with_empty_liquidity_reward
docs: Accumulated seconds when the farm distributed rewards but the bin was empty.
These rewards will be carried over to the next reward time window.
